The paper deals with the problem of efficiently storing and accessing the output of relational queries, which is a core problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel parameterized data structure that can be tuned to trade off space for answer time, which involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between minimizing space and minimizing answer time, which is a common theme in distributed computing (cs.DC) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
